The paper deals with the security of passwords and their distribution, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses user behavior and how it affects password selection, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of statistics and algorithms to analyze password distributions also falls under the category of computational complexity and algorithms (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning to shape password distributions, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
